<Base title="About Us" lang="en" description="The history of the Szent László Hungarian School in Vancouver, from 1960 to today.">
  <div class="container container--narrow prose">
    <h1 class="page-title">Our School's History</h1>

    <img src="/images/rolunk-tortenet.jpg" alt="An old photograph from the school's life" style="border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;" />

    <p>
      The Szent László Hungarian School was founded in 1960, shortly after the
      establishment of the Our Lady of Hungary parish. Ever since, the school has
      operated in the building attached to the Our Lady of Hungary Catholic Church
      whenever classes are held in person. We have a very well-equipped kindergarten
      room and three additional classrooms at our disposal; one of the rooms also
      houses a small library.
    </p>
    <p>
      In the early years, around 30 children attended the school, taught by four or
      five teachers. Many of those children stayed in the community and later joined
      the school's work as teachers or volunteers. Enrollment varies from year to
      year — sometimes more children sign up, sometimes fewer. To this day, both the
      teachers and the helpers work as volunteers.
    </p>
    <p>
      From 1960 the principal was Sándor Murguly, followed in 1995 by Dr. Gabriella
      Horváth, who said farewell to the school at the end of the 2022 school year.
      Until 2010 Gabriella also supported the school as a teacher alongside her
      administrative duties. Since May 2022, the Szent László Hungarian School has
      been led by Emőke Madár.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
